value.0: This looks like an old spellbook, well-loved until the point until someone or something began tearing out the pages. Looking nearby you think you can identify the remnants of its former contents among the refuse.

You barely manage to crack the door before a nauseating stench hits you. The dim light from the nearby fire affords a look at a festering wallow of filth the beastmen call a hut, walls plastered with blood and vomit. A lingering smell of stale urine follows you even after you back away.

Below the oppressive heat at last, you breathe a small sigh of relief only to choke on the foul air down here. In the unmoving stagnant air the stench has intensified tenfold, and your humidity-soaked clothes do nothing but absorb the odor. You wonder just how long it'll take before you no longer smell of rot and feces.
